    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2354747">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2354747">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2354747)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2354747">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djoric" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(388108); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=388108&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203958" alt="Djoric" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=388108)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djoric" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(388108); return false;" >Djoric</a></span> <span class="odate time_1439174624 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Aug 2015 02:43</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2354747">
									

<p>Right then. There's a good deal of reference to other pieces of work, most specifically the Daevic flashbacks of ETDP's Empire of Dirt arc and to <a href="/beneath-two-trees">Beneath Two Trees</a>. And a little bit of <a href="/when-we-came-home">When We Came Home</a></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">More</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Less</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The most important grounding bit is the reference to Ab-Leshal. This is Able / Hevel Ab-Leshal / Hevel the Butcher. Able's crowning moment is his march to the west, wherein he beat down the grumbling border provinces, smashed down basically everyone else on the continent, returned to his homeland, murdered his parents and kin, shattered Hakhama (the Brass/Broken Goddess), tore up the Tree of Life, and returned to Daevon in triumph.</p>
<p>Able's glorious return (bringing with him both a source of immortality and the corpse of one of the Daevite pantheon's great rivals. And Cain, as a slave.) exacerbated the situation described here. Tensions got very, very high, and the high priests' control of Able was waning, as was what remained of his sanity.</p>
<p>Here, we have two events happening at the same time, though their sources aren't really linked.</p>
<p>1) The disciples of the Flesh ended up releasing / birthing their god, which of course began consuming the world.</p>
<p>2) Able goes batshit insane and starts murdering <em>everything</em></p>
<p>So the capital of Daevon is burning, and all those governors and subjugated peoples start rising up and fighting the Empire, themselves, and each other. The Empire is shitting the bed and falling apart. Able murders most of the priesthood &amp; nobility, topples the temples of all the other gods.</p>
<p>Moloch sees this as his opportunity. He is, as described here, &quot;ascendant&quot; - he's gotten very powerful and popular very quickly, and sees Able as a rival and a threat to his position, because Able has also gotten very popular and powerful very quickly, and Moloch wants all that sweet sweet soldier-cult devotion.</p>
<p>So Moloch manifests and leads a counter-attack against Able, who has basically murdered everything in the capital and surrounding area besides the encroaching Flesh, which has gone full-Gravemind world-fucking at this point.</p>
<p>Moloch gets the shit killed out of him, as does his army. Able is triumphant.</p>
<p>And then Able does something magnificently, beautifully stupid.</p>
<p>He goes ahead and gets the Scarlet King's attention.</p>
<p>Like, full-on Warboy &quot;WITNESS ME&quot; attention getting.</p>
<p>You don't want the Scarlet King witnessing you.</p>
<p>The Scarlet King actually starts manifesting. This is the end of the world right here, and ahead of schedule - there's nothing in creation to stop the King from totally winning here.</p>
<p>So instead, there's a cheat. A reset. One time only, possibly divine influence, possibly something else, no one is sure. The King is driven away from Yesod (the baseline universe and all of its facets) Magic is made hidden and difficult where it once was abundant and simple. The world is undone and redone into the one that we know today. The Daevites are removed from the timeline (The last remaining high mages and archmages of the Empire conspire together with SCP-582 to create the Chronicle so that they might return), magic is gone, all of history progresses as normal.</p>
<p>This lasts until 2026, when the Veil that hid magic was stressed so far beyond its design (the world should have 'ended' in the 1940s, with the gathering of the 36, who would have begun preparations to fight off the King properly at the end of time. Foundation really screwed the pooch there.) Everything falls back into &quot;magic everywhere&quot;, human civilization collapses and rebuilds and adapts, and manages to last until 2068.</p>
<p>Which is when someone takes the Chronicle, throws it in the ocean, and brings the world back to what it was like at the very end of the Daevas' rule.</p>
<p>Then we get the return of the King.</p>
<p>So yeah. Context!</p>
<p>e: the gods mentioned are as follows</p>
<p>Scarlet King = self explanatory<br />
Flesh = SCP-610<br />
Ana = SCP-1052<br />
The Crucible = The Factory<br />
Moloch = SCP-089<br />
The Hanged King = SCP-701<br />
The Mother = SCP-597<br />
Buried Giants = SCP-1193</p>
<p>e: And lo, I forgot to actually explain the tale itself.</p>
<p>It's about religious-political tension in the Daevite Empire. The pilgrim came from afar to visit a famous temple of Ana, ate / vomited a last meal of great worth and expense, and then attacked the nearby temple of the Flesh.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><em>Please collapse long posts. ~Zyn</em></p>

